result.execSummary:
All charges against Billy J Cannon III in this case have been dismissed. These charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Billy J Cannon III is presumed innocent.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: 01:43 PM Defendant Billy J Cannon in court.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  State moves to dismiss.  Court order case dismissed.    Cash bail previously posted to be refunded to poster.  Cash bail and surety bond are voided.

Defendant to comply with I.D. Processing.  COURT ORDERED A $2,500.00 CASH BOND (PREVIOUSLY POSTED) IN ADDITION TO A $10,000.00 SIGNATURE BOND TO BE CO-SIGNED WITH HIS MOTHER, CELIA JONES.

01:37 PM District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Billy J Cannon in court.  The defendant states he has not yet gone to Illinois.  Defendants mother appeared in Court stating there has been some confusion and they were told he did not need to go to Illinois.  The Court takes recess at 1:42 pm so the State may look into this matter and why this case is back before this Court.   

Case recalled at 2:06 pm.  Ted Szczupakiewicz appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Billy J Cannon in court.  Attorney Szczupakiewicz states the defendant waived his right to extradition at the previous Court date at which time the Court set cash bail and the defendant posted.  Attorney Szczupakiewicz requests the defendants bail be revoked and be taken into custody to wait for the State of Illinois to pick up the defendant as he already did waive his right to contest the extradition.  The Court is notified by the Sheriff's Dept that the warrant is still in effect in the State of Illionis.  The Court will modify the bond to add a $10,000 surety bond in addition to the $2,500.00 cash bond already posted.  Defendant's mother, Celia Jones is to sign the bond and ensure the defendant goes to Illinois to take care of the warrant there.  The Court will further set a date this Friday to ensure the defendant has reported to Illionis.  The Court adjourns 20CM360 to this Friday.  Hearing scheduled for April 8, 2022 at 01:00 pm.
**AMENDED** Affidavit In Support of Extradition signed by DDA Szczupakiewicz.

01:23 PM Defendant Billy J Cannon in court, in custody, with attorney  State Public Defender Law Intern, as a friend of the court.   Patrick Ryan Campbell appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Atty. Longoria states the defendant has hired private counsel.    Defense acknowledges receipt of complaint and waives reading of complaint.  Service admitted/advised of charges and potential penalties.  Defendant agrees to sign the waiver of extradition.  Check Case scheduled for April 5, 2022.
